      • serialConfigure

        public void serialConfigure​(java.util.ArrayList<ProductionRecord> productionLog)
        This method is used to garner the production runs that exist in the Database. It then performs operations until the highest value serial number of each itemType is gotten so that the system can maintain proper serial number generation. Most of the variables here are local and are only used here and may not have the most intuitive/meaningful names.

        Updated Functionality: This method is also used to get the max "Production Number" value from the production log so that the subsequent created ProductionRecord will continue sequentially.

        Parameters:
        productionLog - this is an ArrayList that contains everything from the PRODUCTIONRECORD database
